#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:5
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "設定"

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:7
msgid ""
"The Scrapy settings allows you to customize the behaviour of all Scrapy "
"components, including the core, extensions, pipelines and spiders themselves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:10
msgid ""
"The infrastructure of the settings provides a global namespace of key-value "
"mappings that the code can use to pull configuration values from. The "
"settings can be populated through different mechanisms, which are described "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:14
msgid ""
"The settings are also the mechanism for selecting the currently active "
"Scrapy project (in case you have many)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:17
msgid ""
"For a list of available built-in settings see: :ref:`topics-settings-ref`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:22
msgid "Designating the settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:24
msgid ""
"When you use Scrapy, you have to tell it which settings you're using. You "
"can do this by using an environment variable, ``SCRAPY_SETTINGS_MODULE``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:27
msgid ""
"The value of ``SCRAPY_SETTINGS_MODULE`` should be in Python path syntax, e."
"g. ``myproject.settings``. Note that the settings module should be on the "
"Python `import search path`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:36
msgid "Populating the settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:38
msgid ""
"Settings can be populated using different mechanisms, each of which having a "
"different precedence. Here is the list of them in decreasing order of "
"precedence:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:42
msgid "Command line options (most precedence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:43
msgid "Settings per-spider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:44
msgid "Project settings module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:45
msgid "Default settings per-command"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:46
msgid "Default global settings (less precedence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:48
msgid ""
"The population of these settings sources is taken care of internally, but a "
"manual handling is possible using API calls. See the :ref:`topics-api-"
"settings` topic for reference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:52
msgid "These mechanisms are described in more detail below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:55
msgid "1. Command line options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:57
msgid ""
"Arguments provided by the command line are the ones that take most "
"precedence, overriding any other options. You can explicitly override one "
"(or more) settings using the ``-s`` (or ``--set``) command line option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:63 ../../../topics/settings.rst:841
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:980 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1046
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1073 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1344
msgid "Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:65
msgid "scrapy crawl myspider -s LOG_FILE=scrapy.log"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:68
msgid "2. Settings per-spider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:70
msgid ""
"Spiders (See the :ref:`topics-spiders` chapter for reference) can define "
"their own settings that will take precedence and override the project ones. "
"They can do so by setting their :attr:`~scrapy.spiders.Spider."
"custom_settings` attribute::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:74
msgid ""
"class MySpider(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = 'myspider'\n"
"\n"
"    custom_settings = {\n"
"        'SOME_SETTING': 'some value',\n"
"    }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:82
msgid "3. Project settings module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:84
msgid ""
"The project settings module is the standard configuration file for your "
"Scrapy project, it's where most of your custom settings will be populated. "
"For a standard Scrapy project, this means you'll be adding or changing the "
"settings in the ``settings.py`` file created for your project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:90
msgid "4. Default settings per-command"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:92
msgid ""
"Each :doc:`Scrapy tool </topics/commands>` command can have its own default "
"settings, which override the global default settings. Those custom command "
"settings are specified in the ``default_settings`` attribute of the command "
"class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:98
msgid "5. Default global settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:100
msgid ""
"The global defaults are located in the ``scrapy.settings.default_settings`` "
"module and documented in the :ref:`topics-settings-ref` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:104
msgid "How to access settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:108
msgid "In a spider, the settings are available through ``self.settings``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:110
msgid ""
"class MySpider(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = 'myspider'\n"
"    start_urls = ['http://example.com']\n"
"\n"
"    def parse(self, response):\n"
"        print(\"Existing settings: %s\" % self.settings.attributes.keys())"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:118
msgid ""
"The ``settings`` attribute is set in the base Spider class after the spider "
"is initialized.  If you want to use the settings before the initialization "
"(e.g., in your spider's ``__init__()`` method), you'll need to override the :"
"meth:`~scrapy.spiders.Spider.from_crawler` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:123
msgid ""
"Settings can be accessed through the :attr:`scrapy.crawler.Crawler.settings` "
"attribute of the Crawler that is passed to ``from_crawler`` method in "
"extensions, middlewares and item pipelines::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:127
msgid ""
"class MyExtension(object):\n"
"    def __init__(self, log_is_enabled=False):\n"
"        if log_is_enabled:\n"
"            print(\"log is enabled!\")\n"
"\n"
"    @classmethod\n"
"    def from_crawler(cls, crawler):\n"
"        settings = crawler.settings\n"
"        return cls(settings.getbool('LOG_ENABLED'))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:137
msgid ""
"The settings object can be used like a dict (e.g., "
"``settings['LOG_ENABLED']``), but it's usually preferred to extract the "
"setting in the format you need it to avoid type errors, using one of the "
"methods provided by the :class:`~scrapy.settings.Settings` API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:143
msgid "Rationale for setting names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:145
msgid ""
"Setting names are usually prefixed with the component that they configure. "
"For example, proper setting names for a fictional robots.txt extension would "
"be ``ROBOTSTXT_ENABLED``, ``ROBOTSTXT_OBEY``, ``ROBOTSTXT_CACHEDIR``, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:153
msgid "Built-in settings reference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:155
msgid ""
"Here's a list of all available Scrapy settings, in alphabetical order, along "
"with their default values and the scope where they apply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:158
msgid ""
"The scope, where available, shows where the setting is being used, if it's "
"tied to any particular component. In that case the module of that component "
"will be shown, typically an extension, middleware or pipeline. It also means "
"that the component must be enabled in order for the setting to have any "
"effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:166
msgid "AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:168 ../../../topics/settings.rst:178
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:188 ../../../topics/settings.rst:198
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:209 ../../../topics/settings.rst:219
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:881 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1170
msgid "Default: ``None``"
msgstr "預設值：``None``"

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:170
msgid ""
"The AWS access key used by code that requires access to `Amazon Web "
"services`_, such as the :ref:`S3 feed storage backend <topics-feed-storage-"
"s3>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:176
msgid "AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:180
msgid ""
"The AWS secret key used by code that requires access to `Amazon Web "
"services`_, such as the :ref:`S3 feed storage backend <topics-feed-storage-"
"s3>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:186
msgid "AWS_ENDPOINT_URL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:190
msgid ""
"Endpoint URL used for S3-like storage, for example Minio or s3.scality. Only "
"supported with ``botocore`` library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:196
msgid "AWS_USE_SSL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:200
msgid ""
"Use this option if you want to disable SSL connection for communication with "
"S3 or S3-like storage. By default SSL will be used. Only supported with "
"``botocore`` library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:207
msgid "AWS_VERIFY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:211
msgid ""
"Verify SSL connection between Scrapy and S3 or S3-like storage. By default "
"SSL verification will occur. Only supported with ``botocore`` library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:217
msgid "AWS_REGION_NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:221
msgid ""
"The name of the region associated with the AWS client. Only supported with "
"``botocore`` library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:227
msgid "BOT_NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:229
msgid "Default: ``'scrapybot'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:231
msgid ""
"The name of the bot implemented by this Scrapy project (also known as the "
"project name). This name will be used for the logging too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:234
msgid ""
"It's automatically populated with your project name when you create your "
"project with the :command:`startproject` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:240
msgid "CONCURRENT_ITEMS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:242
msgid "Default: ``100``"
msgstr "預設值：``100``"

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:244
msgid ""
"Maximum number of concurrent items (per response) to process in parallel in "
"the Item Processor (also known as the :ref:`Item Pipeline <topics-item-"
"pipeline>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:250
msgid "CONCURRENT_REQUESTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:252
msgid "Default: ``16``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:254
msgid ""
"The maximum number of concurrent (ie. simultaneous) requests that will be "
"performed by the Scrapy downloader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:260
msgid "CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_DOMAIN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:262
msgid "Default: ``8``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:264
msgid ""
"The maximum number of concurrent (ie. simultaneous) requests that will be "
"performed to any single domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:267
msgid ""
"See also: :ref:`topics-autothrottle` and its :setting:"
"`AUTOTHROTTLE_TARGET_CONCURRENCY` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:274
msgid "CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_IP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:276 ../../../topics/settings.rst:319
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:331 ../../../topics/settings.rst:560
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1006 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1057
msgid "Default: ``0``"
msgstr "預設值：``0``"

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:278
msgid ""
"The maximum number of concurrent (ie. simultaneous) requests that will be "
"performed to any single IP. If non-zero, the :setting:"
"`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_DOMAIN` setting is ignored, and this one is used "
"instead. In other words, concurrency limits will be applied per IP, not per "
"domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:284
msgid ""
"This setting also affects :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY` and :ref:`topics-"
"autothrottle`: if :setting:`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_IP` is non-zero, "
"download delay is enforced per IP, not per domain."
msgstr ""

