msgid "DOWNLOADER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:396
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.core.downloader.Downloader'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:398
msgid "The downloader to use for crawling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:403
msgid "DOWNLOADER_HTTPCLIENTFACTORY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:405
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.core.downloader.webclient.ScrapyHTTPClientFactory'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:407
msgid ""
"Defines a Twisted ``protocol.ClientFactory``  class to use for HTTP/1.0 "
"connections (for ``HTTP10DownloadHandler``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:412
msgid ""
"HTTP/1.0 is rarely used nowadays so you can safely ignore this setting, "
"unless you use Twisted<11.1, or if you really want to use HTTP/1.0 and "
"override :setting:`DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS_BASE` for ``http(s)`` scheme "
"accordingly, i.e. to ``'scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.http."
"HTTP10DownloadHandler'``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:421
msgid "DOWNLOADER_CLIENTCONTEXTFACTORY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:423
msgid ""
"Default: ``'scrapy.core.downloader.contextfactory."
"ScrapyClientContextFactory'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:425
msgid "Represents the classpath to the ContextFactory to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:427
msgid ""
"Here, \"ContextFactory\" is a Twisted term for SSL/TLS contexts, defining "
"the TLS/SSL protocol version to use, whether to do certificate verification, "
"or even enable client-side authentication (and various other things)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:433
msgid ""
"Scrapy default context factory **does NOT perform remote server certificate "
"verification**. This is usually fine for web scraping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:436
msgid ""
"If you do need remote server certificate verification enabled, Scrapy also "
"has another context factory class that you can set, ``'scrapy.core."
"downloader.contextfactory.BrowserLikeContextFactory'``, which uses the "
"platform's certificates to validate remote endpoints. **This is only "
"available if you use Twisted>=14.0.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:442
msgid ""
"If you do use a custom ContextFactory, make sure its ``__init__`` method "
"accepts a ``method`` parameter (this is the ``OpenSSL.SSL`` method mapping :"
"setting:`DOWNLOADER_CLIENT_TLS_METHOD`), a ``tls_verbose_logging`` parameter "
"(``bool``) and a ``tls_ciphers`` parameter (see :setting:"
"`DOWNLOADER_CLIENT_TLS_CIPHERS`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:451
msgid "DOWNLOADER_CLIENT_TLS_CIPHERS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:453
msgid "Default: ``'DEFAULT'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:455
msgid ""
"Use  this setting to customize the TLS/SSL ciphers used by the default "
"HTTP/1.1 downloader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:458
msgid ""
"The setting should contain a string in the `OpenSSL cipher list format`_, "
"these ciphers will be used as client ciphers. Changing this setting may be "
"necessary to access certain HTTPS websites: for example, you may need to use "
"``'DEFAULT:!DH'`` for a website with weak DH parameters or enable a specific "
"cipher that is not included in ``DEFAULT`` if a website requires it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:469
msgid "DOWNLOADER_CLIENT_TLS_METHOD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:471
msgid "Default: ``'TLS'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:473
msgid ""
"Use this setting to customize the TLS/SSL method used by the default "
"HTTP/1.1 downloader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:476
msgid "This setting must be one of these string values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:478
msgid ""
"``'TLS'``: maps to OpenSSL's ``TLS_method()`` (a.k.a ``SSLv23_method()``), "
"which allows protocol negotiation, starting from the highest supported by "
"the platform; **default, recommended**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:481
msgid ""
"``'TLSv1.0'``: this value forces HTTPS connections to use TLS version 1.0 ; "
"set this if you want the behavior of Scrapy<1.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:483
msgid "``'TLSv1.1'``: forces TLS version 1.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:484
msgid "``'TLSv1.2'``: forces TLS version 1.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:485
msgid "``'SSLv3'``: forces SSL version 3 (**not recommended**)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:489
msgid ""
"We recommend that you use PyOpenSSL>=0.13 and Twisted>=0.13 or above "
"(Twisted>=14.0 if you can)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:495
msgid "DOWNLOADER_CLIENT_TLS_VERBOSE_LOGGING"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:499
msgid ""
"Setting this to ``True`` will enable DEBUG level messages about TLS "
"connection parameters after establishing HTTPS connections. The kind of "
"information logged depends on the versions of OpenSSL and pyOpenSSL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:503
msgid ""
"This setting is only used for the default :setting:"
"`DOWNLOADER_CLIENTCONTEXTFACTORY`."
msgstr ""

