"A dict containing the downloader middlewares enabled by default in Scrapy. "
"Low orders are closer to the engine, high orders are closer to the "
"downloader. You should never modify this setting in your project, modify :"
"setting:`DOWNLOADER_MIDDLEWARES` instead.  For more info see :ref:`topics-"
"downloader-middleware-setting`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:549
msgid "DOWNLOADER_STATS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:553
msgid "Whether to enable downloader stats collection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:558
msgid "DOWNLOAD_DELAY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:562
msgid ""
"The amount of time (in secs) that the downloader should wait before "
"downloading consecutive pages from the same website. This can be used to "
"throttle the crawling speed to avoid hitting servers too hard. Decimal "
"numbers are supported.  Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:567
msgid "DOWNLOAD_DELAY = 0.25    # 250 ms of delay"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:569
msgid ""
"This setting is also affected by the :setting:`RANDOMIZE_DOWNLOAD_DELAY` "
"setting (which is enabled by default). By default, Scrapy doesn't wait a "
"fixed amount of time between requests, but uses a random interval between "
"0.5 * :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY` and 1.5 * :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:573
msgid ""
"When :setting:`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_IP` is non-zero, delays are enforced "
"per ip address instead of per domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:578
msgid ""
"You can also change this setting per spider by setting ``download_delay`` "
"spider attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:584
msgid "DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:586 ../../../topics/settings.rst:835
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:853
msgid "Default: ``{}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:588
msgid ""
"A dict containing the request downloader handlers enabled in your project. "
"See :setting:`DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS_BASE` for example format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:594
msgid "DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS_BASE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:598
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    'file': 'scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.file.FileDownloadHandler',\n"
"    'http': 'scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.http.HTTPDownloadHandler',\n"
"    'https': 'scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.http.HTTPDownloadHandler',\n"
"    's3': 'scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.s3.S3DownloadHandler',\n"
"    'ftp': 'scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.ftp.FTPDownloadHandler',\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:607
msgid ""
"A dict containing the request download handlers enabled by default in "
"Scrapy. You should never modify this setting in your project, modify :"
"setting:`DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:611
msgid ""
"You can disable any of these download handlers by assigning ``None`` to "
"their URI scheme in :setting:`DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS`. E.g., to disable the built-"
"in FTP handler (without replacement), place this in your ``settings.py``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:615
msgid ""
"DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS = {\n"
"    'ftp': None,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:622
msgid "DOWNLOAD_TIMEOUT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:624
msgid "Default: ``180``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:626
msgid ""
"The amount of time (in secs) that the downloader will wait before timing out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:630
msgid ""
"This timeout can be set per spider using :attr:`download_timeout` spider "
"attribute and per-request using :reqmeta:`download_timeout` Request.meta key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:638
msgid "DOWNLOAD_MAXSIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:640
msgid "Default: ``1073741824`` (1 GiB)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:642
msgid ""
"The maximum response body size (in bytes) allowed. Bigger responses are "
"aborted and ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:645
msgid ""
"This applies both before and after compression. If decompressing a response "
"body would exceed this limit, decompression is aborted and the response is "
"ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:649 ../../../topics/settings.rst:668
msgid "Use ``0`` to disable this limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:651
msgid ""
"This limit can be set per spider using the :attr:`download_maxsize` spider "
"attribute and per request using the :reqmeta:`download_maxsize` Request.meta "
"key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:655 ../../../topics/settings.rst:674
msgid "This feature needs Twisted >= 11.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:661
msgid "DOWNLOAD_WARNSIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:663
msgid "Default: ``33554432`` (32 MiB)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:665
msgid ""
"If the size of a response exceeds this value, before or after compression, a "
"warning will be logged about it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:670
msgid ""
"This limit can be set per spider using the :attr:`download_warnsize` spider "
"attribute and per request using the :reqmeta:`download_warnsize` Request."
"meta key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:679
msgid "DOWNLOAD_FAIL_ON_DATALOSS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:683
msgid ""
"Whether or not to fail on broken responses, that is, declared ``Content-"
"Length`` does not match content sent by the server or chunked response was "
"not properly finish. If ``True``, these responses raise a "
"``ResponseFailed([_DataLoss])`` error. If ``False``, these responses are "
"passed through and the flag ``dataloss`` is added to the response, i.e.: "
"``'dataloss' in response.flags`` is ``True``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:690
msgid ""
"Optionally, this can be set per-request basis by using the :reqmeta:"
"`download_fail_on_dataloss` Request.meta key to ``False``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:695
msgid ""
"A broken response, or data loss error, may happen under several "
"circumstances, from server misconfiguration to network errors to data "
"corruption. It is up to the user to decide if it makes sense to process "
"broken responses considering they may contain partial or incomplete content. "
"If :setting:`RETRY_ENABLED` is ``True`` and this setting is set to ``True``, "
"the ``ResponseFailed([_DataLoss])`` failure will be retried as usual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:705
msgid "DUPEFILTER_CLASS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:707
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.dupefilters.RFPDupeFilter'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:709
msgid "The class used to detect and filter duplicate requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:711
msgid ""
"The default (``RFPDupeFilter``) filters based on request fingerprint using "
"the ``scrapy.utils.request.request_fingerprint`` function. In order to "
"change the way duplicates are checked you could subclass ``RFPDupeFilter`` "
"and override its ``request_fingerprint`` method. This method should accept "
"scrapy :class:`~scrapy.http.Request` object and return its fingerprint (a "
"string)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:718
msgid ""
"You can disable filtering of duplicate requests by setting :setting:"
"`DUPEFILTER_CLASS` to ``'scrapy.dupefilters.BaseDupeFilter'``. Be very "
"careful about this however, because you can get into crawling loops. It's "
"usually a better idea to set the ``dont_filter`` parameter to ``True`` on "
"the specific :class:`~scrapy.http.Request` that should not be filtered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:728
msgid "DUPEFILTER_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:732
msgid ""
"By default, ``RFPDupeFilter`` only logs the first duplicate request. "
"Setting :setting:`DUPEFILTER_DEBUG` to ``True`` will make it log all "
"duplicate requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:738
msgid "EDITOR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:740
msgid "Default: ``vi`` (on Unix systems) or the IDLE editor (on Windows)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:742
msgid ""
"The editor to use for editing spiders with the :command:`edit` command. "
"Additionally, if the ``EDITOR`` environment variable is set, the :command:"
"`edit` command will prefer it over the default setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:749
msgid "EXTENSIONS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:753
msgid ""
"A dict containing the extensions enabled in your project, and their orders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:758
msgid "EXTENSIONS_BASE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:762
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.corestats.CoreStats': 0,\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.telnet.TelnetConsole': 0,\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.memusage.MemoryUsage': 0,\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.memdebug.MemoryDebugger': 0,\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.closespider.CloseSpider': 0,\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.feedexport.FeedExporter': 0,\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.logstats.LogStats': 0,\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.spiderstate.SpiderState': 0,\n"
"    'scrapy.extensions.throttle.AutoThrottle': 0,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:774
msgid ""
"A dict containing the extensions available by default in Scrapy, and their "
"orders. This setting contains all stable built-in extensions. Keep in mind "
"that some of them need to be enabled through a setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:778
msgid ""
"For more information See the :ref:`extensions user guide  <topics-"
"extensions>` and the :ref:`list of available extensions <topics-extensions-"
"ref>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:785
msgid "FEED_TEMPDIR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:787
msgid ""
"The Feed Temp dir allows you to set a custom folder to save crawler "
"temporary files before uploading with :ref:`FTP feed storage <topics-feed-"
"storage-ftp>` and :ref:`Amazon S3 <topics-feed-storage-s3>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:794
msgid "FTP_PASSIVE_MODE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:798
msgid "Whether or not to use passive mode when initiating FTP transfers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:804
msgid "FTP_PASSWORD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:806
msgid "Default: ``\"guest\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:808
msgid ""
"The password to use for FTP connections when there is no "
"``\"ftp_password\"`` in ``Request`` meta."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:812
msgid ""
"Paraphrasing `RFC 1635`_, although it is common to use either the password "
"\"guest\" or one's e-mail address for anonymous FTP, some FTP servers "
"explicitly ask for the user's e-mail address and will not allow login with "
"the \"guest\" password."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:823
msgid "FTP_USER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:825
msgid "Default: ``\"anonymous\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:827
msgid ""
"The username to use for FTP connections when there is no ``\"ftp_user\"`` in "
"``Request`` meta."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:833
msgid "ITEM_PIPELINES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:837
msgid ""
"A dict containing the item pipelines to use, and their orders. Order values "
"are arbitrary, but it is customary to define them in the 0-1000 range. Lower "
"orders process before higher orders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:843
msgid ""
"ITEM_PIPELINES = {\n"
"    'mybot.pipelines.validate.ValidateMyItem': 300,\n"
"    'mybot.pipelines.validate.StoreMyItem': 800,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:851
msgid "ITEM_PIPELINES_BASE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:855
msgid ""
"A dict containing the pipelines enabled by default in Scrapy. You should "
"never modify this setting in your project, modify :setting:`ITEM_PIPELINES` "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:861
msgid "LOG_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:865
msgid "Whether to enable logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:870
msgid "LOG_ENCODING"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:872
msgid "Default: ``'utf-8'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:874
msgid "The encoding to use for logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:879
msgid "LOG_FILE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:883
msgid ""
"File name to use for logging output. If ``None``, standard error will be "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:888
msgid "LOG_FORMAT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:890
msgid "Default: ``'%(asctime)s [%(name)s] %(levelname)s: %(message)s'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:892
msgid ""
"String for formatting log messsages. Refer to the `Python logging "
"documentation`_ for the whole list of available placeholders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:900
msgid "LOG_DATEFORMAT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:902
msgid "Default: ``'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:904
msgid ""
"String for formatting date/time, expansion of the ``%(asctime)s`` "
"placeholder in :setting:`LOG_FORMAT`. Refer to the `Python datetime "
"documentation`_ for the whole list of available directives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:913
msgid "LOG_FORMATTER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:915
msgid "Default: :class:`scrapy.logformatter.LogFormatter`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:917
msgid ""
"The class to use for :ref:`formatting log messages <custom-log-formats>` for "
"different actions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:922
msgid "LOG_LEVEL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:924
msgid "Default: ``'DEBUG'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:926
msgid ""
"Minimum level to log. Available levels are: CRITICAL, ERROR, WARNING, INFO, "
"DEBUG. For more info see :ref:`topics-logging`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:932
msgid "LOG_STDOUT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:936
msgid ""
"If ``True``, all standard output (and error) of your process will be "
"redirected to the log. For example if you ``print('hello')`` it will appear "
"in the Scrapy log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:943
msgid "LOG_SHORT_NAMES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:947
msgid ""
"If ``True``, the logs will just contain the root path. If it is set to "
"``False`` then it displays the component responsible for the log output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:953
msgid "LOGSTATS_INTERVAL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:955 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1022
msgid "Default: ``60.0``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:957
msgid ""
"The interval (in seconds) between each logging printout of the stats by :"
"class:`~scrapy.extensions.logstats.LogStats`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:963
msgid "MEMDEBUG_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:967
msgid "Whether to enable memory debugging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:972
msgid "MEMDEBUG_NOTIFY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:974 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1340
msgid "Default: ``[]``"
msgstr "預設值：``[]``"

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:976
msgid ""
"When memory debugging is enabled a memory report will be sent to the "
"specified addresses if this setting is not empty, otherwise the report will "
"be written to the log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:982
msgid "MEMDEBUG_NOTIFY = ['user@example.com']"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:987
msgid "MEMUSAGE_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:991 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1008
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1024 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1042
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1059
msgid "Scope: ``scrapy.extensions.memusage``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:993
msgid ""
"Whether to enable the memory usage extension. This extension keeps track of "
"a peak memory used by the process (it writes it to stats). It can also "
"optionally shutdown the Scrapy process when it exceeds a memory limit (see :"
"setting:`MEMUSAGE_LIMIT_MB`), and notify by email when that happened (see :"
"setting:`MEMUSAGE_NOTIFY_MAIL`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:999 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1013
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1033 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1050
msgid "See :ref:`topics-extensions-ref-memusage`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1004
msgid "MEMUSAGE_LIMIT_MB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1010
msgid ""
"The maximum amount of memory to allow (in megabytes) before shutting down "
"Scrapy  (if MEMUSAGE_ENABLED is True). If zero, no check will be performed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1018
msgid "MEMUSAGE_CHECK_INTERVAL_SECONDS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1026
msgid ""
"The :ref:`Memory usage extension <topics-extensions-ref-memusage>` checks "
"the current memory usage, versus the limits set by :setting:"
"`MEMUSAGE_LIMIT_MB` and :setting:`MEMUSAGE_WARNING_MB`, at fixed time "
"intervals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1031
msgid "This sets the length of these intervals, in seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1038
msgid "MEMUSAGE_NOTIFY_MAIL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1044
msgid "A list of emails to notify if the memory limit has been reached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1048
msgid "MEMUSAGE_NOTIFY_MAIL = ['user@example.com']"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1055
msgid "MEMUSAGE_WARNING_MB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1061
msgid ""
"The maximum amount of memory to allow (in megabytes) before sending a "
"warning email notifying about it. If zero, no warning will be produced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1067
msgid "NEWSPIDER_MODULE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1069
msgid "Default: ``''``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1071
msgid ""
"Module where to create new spiders using the :command:`genspider` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1075
msgid "NEWSPIDER_MODULE = 'mybot.spiders_dev'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1080
msgid "RANDOMIZE_DOWNLOAD_DELAY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1084
msgid ""
"If enabled, Scrapy will wait a random amount of time (between 0.5 * :setting:"
"`DOWNLOAD_DELAY` and 1.5 * :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY`) while fetching "
"requests from the same website."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1087
msgid ""
"This randomization decreases the chance of the crawler being detected (and "
"subsequently blocked) by sites which analyze requests looking for "
"statistically significant similarities in the time between their requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1091
msgid ""
"The randomization policy is the same used by `wget`_ ``--random-wait`` "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1093
msgid ""
"If :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY` is zero (default) this option has no effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1100
msgid "REACTOR_THREADPOOL_MAXSIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1102
msgid "Default: ``10``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1104
msgid ""
"The maximum limit for Twisted Reactor thread pool size. This is common multi-"
"purpose thread pool used by various Scrapy components. Threaded DNS "
"Resolver, BlockingFeedStorage, S3FilesStore just to name a few. Increase "
"this value if you're experiencing problems with insufficient blocking IO."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1112
msgid "REDIRECT_PRIORITY_ADJUST"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1114
msgid "Default: ``+2``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1116
msgid "Scope: ``scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.redirect.RedirectMiddleware``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1118
msgid "Adjust redirect request priority relative to original request:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1120
msgid "**a positive priority adjust (default) means higher priority.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1121
msgid "a negative priority adjust means lower priority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1126
msgid "RETRY_PRIORITY_ADJUST"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1128
msgid "Default: ``-1``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1130
msgid "Scope: ``scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.retry.RetryMiddleware``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1132
msgid "Adjust retry request priority relative to original request:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1134
msgid "a positive priority adjust means higher priority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1135
msgid "**a negative priority adjust (default) means lower priority.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1140
msgid "ROBOTSTXT_OBEY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1144
msgid "Scope: ``scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.robotstxt``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1146
msgid ""
"If enabled, Scrapy will respect robots.txt policies. For more information "
"see :ref:`topics-dlmw-robots`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1151
msgid ""
"While the default value is ``False`` for historical reasons, this option is "
"enabled by default in settings.py file generated by ``scrapy startproject`` "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1158
msgid "ROBOTSTXT_PARSER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1160
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.robotstxt.ProtegoRobotParser'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1162
msgid ""
"The parser backend to use for parsing ``robots.txt`` files. For more "
"information see :ref:`topics-dlmw-robots`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1168
msgid "ROBOTSTXT_USER_AGENT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1172
msgid ""
"The user agent string to use for matching in the robots.txt file. If "
"``None``, the User-Agent header you are sending with the request or the :"
"setting:`USER_AGENT` setting (in that order) will be used for determining "
"the user agent to use in the robots.txt file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1180
msgid "SCHEDULER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1182
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.core.scheduler.Scheduler'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1184
msgid "The scheduler to use for crawling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1189
msgid "SCHEDULER_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1193
msgid ""
"Setting to ``True`` will log debug information about the requests scheduler. "
"This currently logs (only once) if the requests cannot be serialized to "
"disk. Stats counter (``scheduler/unserializable``) tracks the number of "
"times this happens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1197
msgid "Example entry in logs::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1199
msgid ""
"1956-01-31 00:00:00+0800 [scrapy.core.scheduler] ERROR: Unable to serialize "
"request:\n"
"<GET http://example.com> - reason: cannot serialize <Request at 0x9a7c7ec>\n"
"(type Request)> - no more unserializable requests will be logged\n"
"(see 'scheduler/unserializable' stats counter)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1208
msgid "SCHEDULER_DISK_QUEUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1210
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.squeues.PickleLifoDiskQueue'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1212
msgid ""
"Type of disk queue that will be used by scheduler. Other available types are "
"``scrapy.squeues.PickleFifoDiskQueue``, ``scrapy.squeues."
"MarshalFifoDiskQueue``, ``scrapy.squeues.MarshalLifoDiskQueue``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1219
msgid "SCHEDULER_MEMORY_QUEUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1220
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.squeues.LifoMemoryQueue'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1222
msgid ""
"Type of in-memory queue used by scheduler. Other available type is: ``scrapy."
"squeues.FifoMemoryQueue``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1228
msgid "SCHEDULER_PRIORITY_QUEUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1229
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.pqueues.ScrapyPriorityQueue'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1231
msgid ""
"Type of priority queue used by the scheduler. Another available type is "
"``scrapy.pqueues.DownloaderAwarePriorityQueue``. ``scrapy.pqueues."
"DownloaderAwarePriorityQueue`` works better than ``scrapy.pqueues."
"ScrapyPriorityQueue`` when you crawl many different domains in parallel. But "
"currently ``scrapy.pqueues.DownloaderAwarePriorityQueue`` does not work "
"together with :setting:`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_IP`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1241
msgid "SPIDER_CONTRACTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1245
msgid ""
"A dict containing the spider contracts enabled in your project, used for "
"testing spiders. For more info see :ref:`topics-contracts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1251
msgid "SPIDER_CONTRACTS_BASE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1255
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    'scrapy.contracts.default.UrlContract' : 1,\n"
"    'scrapy.contracts.default.ReturnsContract': 2,\n"
"    'scrapy.contracts.default.ScrapesContract': 3,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1261
msgid ""
"A dict containing the scrapy contracts enabled by default in Scrapy. You "
"should never modify this setting in your project, modify :setting:"
"`SPIDER_CONTRACTS` instead. For more info see :ref:`topics-contracts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1265
msgid ""
"You can disable any of these contracts by assigning ``None`` to their class "
"path in :setting:`SPIDER_CONTRACTS`. E.g., to disable the built-in "
"``ScrapesContract``, place this in your ``settings.py``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1269
msgid ""
"SPIDER_CONTRACTS = {\n"
"    'scrapy.contracts.default.ScrapesContract': None,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1276
msgid "SPIDER_LOADER_CLASS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1278
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.spiderloader.SpiderLoader'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1280
msgid ""
"The class that will be used for loading spiders, which must implement the :"
"ref:`topics-api-spiderloader`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1286
msgid "SPIDER_LOADER_WARN_ONLY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1292
msgid ""
"By default, when scrapy tries to import spider classes from :setting:"
"`SPIDER_MODULES`, it will fail loudly if there is any ``ImportError`` "
"exception. But you can choose to silence this exception and turn it into a "
"simple warning by setting ``SPIDER_LOADER_WARN_ONLY = True``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1298
msgid ""
"Some :ref:`scrapy commands <topics-commands>` run with this setting to "
"``True`` already (i.e. they will only issue a warning and will not fail) "
"since they do not actually need to load spider classes to work: :command:"
"`scrapy runspider <runspider>`, :command:`scrapy settings <settings>`, :"
"command:`scrapy startproject <startproject>`, :command:`scrapy version "
"<version>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1309
msgid "SPIDER_MIDDLEWARES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1313
msgid ""
"A dict containing the spider middlewares enabled in your project, and their "
"orders. For more info see :ref:`topics-spider-middleware-setting`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1319
msgid "SPIDER_MIDDLEWARES_BASE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1323
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    'scrapy.spidermiddlewares.httperror.HttpErrorMiddleware': 50,\n"
"    'scrapy.spidermiddlewares.offsite.OffsiteMiddleware': 500,\n"
"    'scrapy.spidermiddlewares.referer.RefererMiddleware': 700,\n"
"    'scrapy.spidermiddlewares.urllength.UrlLengthMiddleware': 800,\n"
"    'scrapy.spidermiddlewares.depth.DepthMiddleware': 900,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1331
msgid ""
"A dict containing the spider middlewares enabled by default in Scrapy, and "
"their orders. Low orders are closer to the engine, high orders are closer to "
"the spider. For more info see :ref:`topics-spider-middleware-setting`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1338
msgid "SPIDER_MODULES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1342
msgid "A list of modules where Scrapy will look for spiders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1346
msgid "SPIDER_MODULES = ['mybot.spiders_prod', 'mybot.spiders_dev']"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1351
msgid "STATS_CLASS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1353
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.statscollectors.MemoryStatsCollector'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1355
msgid ""
"The class to use for collecting stats, who must implement the :ref:`topics-"
"api-stats`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1361
msgid "STATS_DUMP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1365
msgid ""
"Dump the :ref:`Scrapy stats <topics-stats>` (to the Scrapy log) once the "
"spider finishes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1368
msgid "For more info see: :ref:`topics-stats`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1373
msgid "STATSMAILER_RCPTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1375
msgid "Default: ``[]`` (empty list)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1377
msgid ""
"Send Scrapy stats after spiders finish scraping. See :class:`~scrapy."
"extensions.statsmailer.StatsMailer` for more info."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1383
msgid "TELNETCONSOLE_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1387
msgid ""
"A boolean which specifies if the :ref:`telnet console <topics-"
"telnetconsole>` will be enabled (provided its extension is also enabled)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1393
msgid "TEMPLATES_DIR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1395
msgid "Default: ``templates`` dir inside scrapy module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1397
msgid ""
"The directory where to look for templates when creating new projects with :"
"command:`startproject` command and new spiders with :command:`genspider` "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1401
msgid ""
"The project name must not conflict with the name of custom files or "
"directories in the ``project`` subdirectory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1408
msgid "URLLENGTH_LIMIT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1410
msgid "Default: ``2083``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1412
msgid "Scope: ``spidermiddlewares.urllength``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1414
msgid ""
"The maximum URL length to allow for crawled URLs. For more information about "
"the default value for this setting see: https://boutell.com/newfaq/misc/"
"urllength.html"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1420
msgid "USER_AGENT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1422
msgid "Default: ``\"Scrapy/VERSION (+https://scrapy.org)\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1424
msgid ""
"The default User-Agent to use when crawling, unless overridden. This user "
"agent is also used by :class:`~scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.robotstxt."
"RobotsTxtMiddleware` if :setting:`ROBOTSTXT_USER_AGENT` setting is ``None`` "
"and there is no overridding User-Agent header specified for the request."
msgstr ""

